6|6}}\n|align=\"left\"|Flower-class corvette\n|align=\"right\"|7 May 1941\n|align=\"right\"|10 May 1941\n|align=\"left\"|3rd <ABBR title=\"Escort Group\">EG</ABBR>\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{HMS|Hollyhock|K64|6}}\n|align=\"left\"|Flower-class corvette\n|align=\"right\"|7 May 1941\n|align=\"right\"|10 May 1941\n|align=\"left\"|3rd <ABBR title=\"Escort Group\">EG</ABBR>\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{HMS|Nigella|K19|6}}\n|align=\"left\"|Flower-class corvette\n|align=\"right\"|7 May 1941\n|align=\"right\"|10 May 1941\n|align=\"left\"|3rd <ABBR title=\"Escort Group\">EG</ABBR>\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{HMT|Daneman|FY123|6}}\n|align=\"left\"|Naval trawler\n|align=\"right\"|7 May 1941\n|align=\"right\"|10 May 1941\n|align=\"left\"|3rd <ABBR title=\"Escort Group\">EG</ABBR>\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{HMT|St Apollo||6}}\n|align=\"left\"|Naval trawler\n|align=\"right\"|7 May 1941\n|align=\"right\"|10 May 1941\n|align=\"left\"|3rd <ABBR title=\"Escort Group\">EG</ABBR>\n|}\n\n===U-boats Hit===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! width=\"100px\"|Date\n! width=\"25px\" |Number\n! width=\"25px\" |Type\n! width=\"200px\"|Commander\n! width=\"25px\" |Casualties\n! width=\"180px\"|Hit by...\n|-\n|align=\"right\" |7/8 May 1941\n|align=\"center\"|{{GS|U-94|1940|2}}\n|align=\"center\"|[[German Type VII submarine#Type VIIC|VIIC]]\n|align=\"left\"  |''Kapit\u00e4nleutnant'' [[Herbert Kuppisch]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uboat.net/men/kuppisch.htm|title=Kapit\u00e4nleutnant Herbert Kuppisch|publisher=www.uboat.net|accessdate=5 November 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"right\" |?\n|align=\"left\"  |Damaged\n|-\n|align=\"right\" |9 May 1941\n|align=\"center\"|{{GS|U-110|1940|2}}<ref>Niestle p120</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|[[German Type IXB submarine|IXB]]\n|align=\"left\"  |''Kapit\u00e4nleutnant'' [[Fritz-Julius Lemp]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uboat.net/men/lemp.htm|title=Kapit\u00e4nleutnant Fritz-Julius Lemp|publisher=www.uboat.net|accessdate=5 November 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"right\" |15\n|align=\"left\"  |''Aubrietia'', {{HMS|Bulldog|H91|2}}, ''Broadway''\n|-\n|align=\"right\" |9 May 1941\n|align=\"center\"|{{GS|U-201||2}}\n|align=\"center\"|[[German Type VII submarine#Type VIIC|VIIC]]\n|align=\"left\"  |''Korvettenkapit\u00e4n'' [[Adalbert Schnee]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uboat.net/men/schnee.htm|title=Korvettenkapit\u00e4n Adalbert Schnee|publisher=www.uboat.net|accessdate=5 November 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"right\" |?\n|align=\"left\"  |Damaged\n|}\n\n==U-571 (film)==\n{{further|U-571 (film)}}\nThe film ''[[U-571 (film)|U-571]]'' was partially inspired by the capture of ''U-110''. The film however caused irritation and anger in Britain whereby the film's plot was Americanised. The anger came to such a point that at [[Prime Minister's Questions]], [[Tony Blair]] agreed with questioner [[Brian Jenkins (politician)|Brian Jenkins MP]] that the film was \"an affront\" to British sailors.<ref name=\"blair\">\n{{cite news|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/781858.stm\n |title = U-boat film an 'affront', says Blair\n |publisher = [[BBC News]]\n |date = 7 June 2000\n |accessdate = 2006-08-18\n\n}}</ref>\nIn response to a letter from [[Paul Truswell]], [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for the [[Pudsey (UK Parliament constituency)|Pudsey]] constituency (which includes [[Horsforth]], a town proud of its connection with HMS ''Aubrietia''), U.S. president [[Bill Clinton]] wrote assuring that the film's plot was only a work of fiction.<ref name=\"bbc-storm\">\n{{cite news|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/773913.stm\n |title = Storm over U-boat film\n |publisher = [[BBC News]]\n |date = 2 June 2000\n |accessdate = 2006-08-18\n}}</ref>\nDespite the criticisms however David Balme was interviewed by the director of the film, [[Jonathan Mostow]] in which he described the capture of ''U-110'' and the capture itself was mentioned at the start of the end credits as recognition and response to the criticisms.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Ultra]]\n* [[Cryptanalysis of the Enigma]]