{"title_page": "Evelyn Hoskins", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Notability|Biography|date=October 2010}}\n{{BLP sources|date=October 2010}}\n}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Evelyn Hoskins\n| image         = \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birthname     =\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1988|5|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[Yeovil]], [[United Kingdom|UK]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| othername     = \n| yearsactive   = \n| homepage      = \n}}\n\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Evelynhoskins.jpg|thumb|alt=Evelyn Hoskins''.]] -->'''Evelyn Hoskins''' (born 13 May 1988 in Yeovil, Somerset) is an English actress best known for her role as Shona Wark in the British BBC1 hospital drama series [[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]].<ref>Evelyn Hoskins, IMDB \"[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3684603/ source 1]\"</ref><ref>BBC Episode guide \"[http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00t15bq source 6]\"</ref>\n\nEvelyn's other television appearances include an appearance in [[Holby City]], also as Shona Wark, and a part in the E4 comedy drama [[Misfits (TV series)|Misfits]] in which she appears as Lucy, a shape-shifter.<ref>Evelyn Hoskins, Spotlight \"[http://www.spotlight.com/interactive/cv/1/F133574.html source 2]\"</ref>\n\nEvelyn attended [[Arts University Bournemouth]] where she graduated with a BA (Hons).<ref>Arts University College Bournemouth \"[http://www.aucb.ac.uk/aboutus/aucbalumni/alumnisuccesses/evehoskins.aspx source 4]\"</ref>\n\nEvelyn's stage debut came playing the part of Thea in [[Spring Awakening (musical)|Spring Awakening]] at the Lyric Hammersmith Theatre on 23 January 2009. Evelyn's other stage appearances include the role of Martha in The Secret Garden at Birmingham Rep and Piper in The Light Princess at The National Theatre Studio.<ref>BBC News \"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/somerset/7802915.stm source 3]\"</ref><ref>Spring Awakening \"[[Spring Awakening (musical)|source 5]]\"</ref>\n\nEvelyn played the role of \"Nicky\" in the 2014 touring production of \"[[This Is My Family]]\".\n\nHoskins has previously played Carrie White in the Southwark Playhouse's production of [[Carrie (musical)|Carrie]].\n\nHoskins also played Cecile Caldwell in [[Cruel Intentions: The Musical (musical)|Cruel Intentions: The Musical]] at the Edinburgh Fringe Festival 2019.\n\nHoskins was engaged to [[Gavin & Stacey|Gavin and Stacey]] actor, [[Mathew Horne]] until 2018.\n\nHoskins finished playing Dawn in the musical Waitress at the Adelphi theatre in 2020. Due to COVID-19 Waitress the Musical closed in London with Hoskins being the final London Dawn, (for now.)\n==Television appearances==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Show !! Character !! Info\n|-\n| [[Holby City]] || Shona Wark || Downstairs Upstairs - (16 February 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || Second Chance (21 November 2009)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || Last Roll of the Dice (23 January 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || The Cradle Will Fall (30 January 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || An Ugly Truth (6 February 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || Love Is a Battlefield (13 February 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || A Better Past (8 May 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || Russian Endings (15 May 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || In Your Debt (5 June 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || Inconvenient Truths (12 June 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || Die and Let Live (26 June 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || Going Solo (10 July 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || I Am Mine (17 July 2010)\n|-\n| Casualty || Shona Wark || What Tonight Means to Me: Part 2 (21 August 2010)\n|-\n| [[Misfits (TV series)|Misfits]] || Lucy || Series 2, episode 1\n|-\n| ''The Sound of Music Live!'' || Liesl von Trapp || UK version of ''[[The Sound of Music Live!]]'' broadcast 20 December 2015\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <r