 station (MBTA)|Wilmington]] and [[North Billerica station|North Billerica]] until January 18, 1965<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.transithistory.org/roster/MBTARouteHistory.pdf|title=Changes to Transit Service in the MBTA district|last=Belcher|first=Jonathan|date=March 14, 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.\n<references />\n[[Category:Wilmington, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Villages in Middlesex County, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Villages in Massachusetts]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the village in Wilmington and Tewksbury|the lake itself|Silver Lake (Wilmington, Massachusetts)|other places named Silver Lake|Silver Lake}}{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = \n| official_name                   = Silver Lake\n| settlement_type                 = [[Populated place]]\n| nickname                        = \"The Lake\"\n| subdivision_type                = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[US State|State]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of counties in Massachusetts|County]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[List of municipalities in Massachusetts|Towns]]\n| named_for                       = [[Silver Lake (Wilmington, Massachusetts)|Silver Lake]]\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|United States}}\n| subdivision_name1               = {{flag|Massachusetts}}\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Middlesex County, Massachusetts|Middlesex]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Wilmington, Massachusetts|Wilmington]], [[Tewksbury, Massachusetts|Tewksbury]]\n| area_code_type                  = \n| area_code                       = 978\n}}\n\n'''Silver Lake''' is an unincorporated village populated place<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://geonames.usgs.gov/apex/f?p=138:3:11197648176500::NO::P3_FID,P3_TITLE:612239,Silver%20Lake|title=GNIS Detail - Silver Lake|website=geonames.usgs.gov|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> in [[Middlesex County, Massachusetts]] in the